== Steak ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry and season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{} (or your favorite grilling spice).

Grill: Grill on oiled grates over medium-high heat to desired doneness (we suggest ~{3-6%minutes} per side, but grills can vary!).

Stovetop: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Let rest a few minutes, then thinly slice against the grain and top with @garlic herb butter{3.5%ounce}.

== Lobster ==

Using #kitchen shears{}, cut along the underside of the @lobster tails{7%ounce}, leaving meat intact and stopping at the tail; pull sides of shell apart to expose meat (do not remove meat from shells). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Grill: Grill, flesh side down, over medium-high heat until grill marks appear and flesh starts to turn opaque. Flip and cook on shell side until lobster is cooked through (we suggest ~{2-3%minutes} per side, but grills can vary!).

Stovetop: Heat a large pan over medium-high heat. Add lobster flesh sides up along with a splash of @water{splash}. Cover and cook until almost cooked through, ~{3%minutes}. Uncover pan and add @butter{2%TBSP}; spoon butter over lobster until cooked through, ~{1%minute}. Using a #chef's knife{}, halve tails lengthwise.

Brush with @garlic herb butter{remaining}.

> Surf & turf isn't just for fancy restaurants anymore. Double the protein, double the fun!